
[1]equitable

   EQ'UITABLE, n. [L. oequitas, from oequus, equal.]

   1. Equal in regard to the rights of persons; distributing equal
   justice; giving each his due; assigning to one or more what law or
   justice demands; just; impartial. The judge does justice by an
   equitable decision. The court will make an equitable distribution of
   the estate.

   2. Having the disposition to do justice, or doing justice; impartial;
   as an equitable judge.

   3. Held or exercised in equity, or with chancery powers; as the
   equitable jurisdiction of a court.
